<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">

    <title>HTML Hyperlinks Demonstration</title>
    
</head>
<body>
    <p>Hyperlinks in HTML are created using the <a> tag with the href attribute to specify the link
        destination. The target attribute determines how the link is opened</p>
    <h3>Basic Hyperlink</h3>
    <p>Visit the<a href="https://www.google.com"> Google </a>website . (Opens in the same tab.)</p>
    <h3>Open Link in a New Tab</h3>
    <p>
        Visit the <a href="https://www.wikipedia.org" target="_blank"> website </a>. (Opens in a new tab.)
    </p>
    <h3>Open Link in Parent Frame</h3>
    <p>
        If this page is inside a frame, visit <a href= "https://www.example.com/" target="_parent"> Example </a>in the parent frame.
    </p>
    <h3>Open Link in Full Window</h3>
    <p>
        Visit <a href="https://www.bbc.com/" target="_top"> BBC News</a> to load in the full browser window.
    </p>
   
</body>

</html>
